The paper focuses on decomposing latent representations in GANs and auto-encoders, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image-to-image translation and object classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions using information-theoretic means to maximize the correlation between factors, which suggests a possible connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions conducting few-shot learning, which is a subfield of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions object classification, which is a task commonly studied in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
